# Resume Match — project rule

## Product
Build a U.S.-focused SaaS called Resume Match.

This is a narrow wedge product:
- user uploads a resume PDF
- user pastes a job description
- app returns:
  - match score
  - missing keywords
  - missing skills
  - ATS risk flags
  - weak bullets
  - rewritten bullets
  - tailored summary
  - premium full rewrite / cover letter behind paywall

This is NOT:
- a job board
- a CRM
- an auto-apply bot
- a browser extension in V1
- a recruiting platform

## Market
Target U.S. job seekers only.
Use English only.
Use USD pricing only.

Initial verticals:
- software engineering
- product
- data / analytics
- design

## Stack
Use:
- Next.js App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Vercel
- Neon Postgres
- Vercel Blob
- Stripe Checkout + Billing
- PostHog
- Sentry
- OpenTelemetry

## AI architecture
Use two-model app architecture:

1. Default runtime model:
- OpenAI GPT-5-mini
- use strict structured JSON output
- use for analysis, extraction, ATS risks, missing keywords, bullet rewrites, tailored summary

2. Premium / fallback runtime model:
- OpenAI GPT-5
- use for full rewrite, cover letter, low-confidence cases, extraction fallback

Never fabricate candidate experience.
Never invent achievements that are not present in the resume.

## Product tone
Tone must be:
- credible
- sharp
- anti-BS
- practical
- not cheesy
- not hype-heavy

Avoid claims like:
- guaranteed interviews
- beat every ATS
- instant job offers

## Monetization
Launch pricing:
- Free: 1 full scan
- Sprint: $12/week
- Pro: $29/month

## Analytics events
